cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.ML 

The paper presents a framework for estimating dependence between numerical features and a categorical label in supervised learning. This topic is closely related to machine learning and statistics, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the broad area of supervised learning. cs.ST (Statistics) is also a likely category as it covers statistical methods for data analysis. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as it covers the study of information processing and communication. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ML (Machine Learning) are also possible categories as they cover various aspects of machine learning and data analysis.
